[30;1m102 | [0m[35m  "definition", which in programming languages refers to the site where a named[0m
[30;1m103 | [0m[35m  object in the universe of the user's program is given some kind of concrete[0m
[30;1m104 | [0m[35m  form).  BodyForm is defined slightly earlier yet (as HelperForm depends on it),[0m

[30;1m54 | [0m[35mIt produces a KLVM expression including a request to run a special primitive (where[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m"primitive" here means an operator installed in the KLVM run time system which is[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35mimplemented in "foreign" (non-KLVM) code) whose function is to produce one step of[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35mchiklisp compilation and wraps this in a KLVM primitive whose purpose is to perform[0m
[30;1m58 | [0m[35moptimization and constant folding.  These are installed in stage_2 (more on this[0m
